<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8897238-elina-sen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1365175533i/8897238._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8897238-elina-sen">Elina Sen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Basho&apos;s was better for me. Well, it had me at the very first page, written there only: &apos;Wake, butterfly-&apos;. Though some of his oft quoted haiku are abs<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Basho's was better for me. Well, it had me at the very first page, written there only: 'Wake, butterfly-'. Though some of his oft quoted haiku are absent. <br /><br />On the other hand, let's not forget, Kenko was no poet, he was rather a austere hermit and some of his thoughts there seemed to me rather borderline misogynistic. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
