  <span id="freeText16658179111794871126" style="display:none">"To be born into this world, it seems, brings with it so much to long for"<br /><br />This book is filled with many pleasant beautiful writings such as this. But at some point it felt to me that it became a ramble of a person who hated everyone else because he knew best how to live, a bit Seneca like. Ah well it's an old book, written in the 1300s, what can you expect? </span>
