    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2832987710" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2832987710" />
    <a title="Paloma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5931265-paloma"><img alt="Paloma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1579496209p2/5931265.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2832987710?book_show_action=true">May 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paloma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paloma" href="/user/show/5931265-paloma">Paloma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5931265-paloma?shelf=owned">owned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5931265-paloma?shelf=reading-challenge-2019">reading-challenge-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5931265-paloma?shelf=classics-cl%C3%A1sicos">classics-clásicos</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5931265-paloma?shelf=literatura-japonesa">literatura-japonesa</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5931265-paloma?shelf=reviewed-rese%C3%B1ados">reviewed-reseñados</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2832987710" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2861826479913901883"><b>Review in Englsh | Reseña en Español</b><br/><br/><i>
  <blockquote> “It is a most wonderful comfort to sit alone beneath a lamp, book spread before you, and commune with someone from the past whom you have never met.”</blockquote>
</i><br/>A little book full of wisdom and deep thoughts, which leave one thinking about truths in life that never cease being relevant. I had never heard of the author, Kenko, a Japanese medieval monk, but most of his reflections remain valid in our times. As most of the Little Black Classics, this collection offers a</span>
  <span id="freeText2861826479913901883" style="display:none"><b>Review in Englsh | Reseña en Español</b><br /><br /><i>
  <blockquote> “It is a most wonderful comfort to sit alone beneath a lamp, book spread before you, and commune with someone from the past whom you have never met.”</blockquote>
</i><br />A little book full of wisdom and deep thoughts, which leave one thinking about truths in life that never cease being relevant. I had never heard of the author, Kenko, a Japanese medieval monk, but most of his reflections remain valid in our times. As most of the Little Black Classics, this collection offers a sample of an author’s work and thus, <i>A cup of Sake Beneath the Cherry Trees</i> give us glimpses of this monk’s teachings on life’s joys and sorrows. <br /><i>
  <blockquote>“If people hate death they should love life. Should we not relish each day the joy of survivial.” </blockquote>
</i><br />And just as the title suggests, going through this book is a wonderful experience that make us think of our approach to life and death, to the attention we pay to our present, and of our attitudes towards others. <br /><i>
  <blockquote>“…it is infinitely more moving to see the moon near dawn and after long anticipation, tinged with the most beautiful palest blue, a moon glimpsed among cedar branches deep in the mountains, its light now hidden again by the gathering of clouds of an autumn shower.”</blockquote>
</i><br />This is a book that does not need to be read in a rush and quite on the contrary –I had to stopped myself from ending it in one sitting, because I wanted the words to really sink in. As I said, there is no particular topic guiding the excerpts presented so we go from learning from the joys of having like-minded friends, to the awareness of seeking deep conversations, passing to the magic of books and the beauty of living in the present and cherishing the life we have now. <br /><br /><i>”What kind of man will feel depressed at being idle? There is nothing finer than to be alone with nothing to distract you.”</i><br />_____<br /><br />Un pequeño libro lleno de sabiduría y reflexiones profunda, que nos deja pensando sobre las verdades de la vida que nunca dejan de ser relevantes. Nunca había oído de este autor, Kenko, un monje japonés medieval, pero la mayoría de sus pensamientos permanecen vigentes hasta nuestros tiempos. <br /><br />Como todos los libros que forman parte de esta comunicación de Penguin, <i>A cup of Sake Beneath the Cherry Trees</i> nos brinda una muestra de las enseñanzas del monje sobre las alegrías y penas de la vida. Y tal como el título sugiere, el camino a través de las páginas de este libro es una experiencia maravillosa que nos invita a reflexionar sobre la vida y la muerte, la atención que le prestamos al presente y las actitudes que tomamos ante los demás. <br /><br />Este es un libro que no necesita leerse apresuradamente; al contrario, en momentos preferí detenerme para no acabarlo en una sola sentada, porque quería poder realmente comprender y disfrutar las palabras en mi espíritu. En la colección no hay un tema o hilo conductor que conecte los extractos, y de la misma manera, vamos de la alegría de contar con amigos que sean afines a nosotros en pensamiento, pasando por la importancia de buscar conversaciones profundas y reflexionado sobre la mágica de los libros y la belleza de vivir en el presente y apreciando la vida que tenemos ahora. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2861826479913901883" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


